A Junonia atlites is a species of butterfly that belongs to the Nymphalidae family. 
The wingspan of a Junonia atlites ranges from 50 to 60 mm. 
The upper side of its wings is orange-brown with black markings and three white spots on each forewing. 
The undersides of its wings are paler with intricate brown and white patterns. 
The body of a Junonia atlites is relatively small and dark brown, with short antennae. 
This butterfly is commonly found in tropical and subtropical areas of the Americas, from the southern United States to Brazil. 
Junonia atlites is often seen near open areas, roadsides, and gardens.
